[Rosie] What are some foods I can eat to help manage my heart failure?
[Educator] Try to limit salt intake and focus on eating plenty of fruits and vegetables.
[Rosie] Can I still eat fried foods?
[Educator] It's best to avoid fried foods as they can be high in unhealthy fats.
[Rosie] What about foods that are high in sugar?
[Educator] It's important to limit foods high in sugar as they can contribute to heart issues.
[Rosie] Are there any specific fruits that are good for my heart?
[Educator] Berries, bananas, and oranges are great choices as they are high in nutrients.
[Rosie] How about vegetables?
[Educator] Dark leafy greens like spinach and kale are excellent for heart health.
[Rosie] Should I be drinking a lot of water?
[Educator] Yes, staying hydrated with water is important for managing heart failure.
[Rosie] Can I still have some snacks between meals?
[Educator] Opt for healthy snacks like nuts, seeds, or yogurt instead of processed snacks.
[Rosie] What about alcohol?
[Educator] It's best to limit alcohol intake as it can worsen heart failure symptoms.
[Rosie] Are there any foods I should completely avoid?
[Educator] Try to avoid processed foods, sugary drinks, and foods high in saturated fats.
[Rosie] How about portion sizes?
[Educator] Pay attention to portion sizes to avoid overeating, which can strain your heart. 
[Rosie] Should I be cooking with a lot of oil?
[Educator] Use heart-healthy oils like olive or avocado oil in moderation when cooking.
[Rosie] Can I still have some dessert occasionally?
[Educator] You can enjoy a small portion of dessert occasionally, but try to choose healthier options. 
